#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn1.37"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn1.37:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 1 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 1 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn1.37:0.2"
msgid "4. Satullapakāyikavagga "
msgstr "4. The Satullapa Group "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn1.37:0.3"
msgid "37. Samayasutta "
msgstr "37. The Congregation "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p><span class="evam">
#. REF: pts1ed1.26, pts2ed1.55, sc1
msgctxt "sn1.37:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—"
msgstr "So I have heard. "

#. HTML: </span>
msgctxt "sn1.37:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sakkesu viharati kapilavatthusmiṃ mahāvane mahatā bhikkhusaṃghena saddhiṃ pañcamattehi bhikkhusatehi sabbeheva arahantehi; "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying in the land of the Sakyans, near Kapilavatthu in the Great Wood, together with a large Saṅgha of around five hundred mendicants, all of whom were perfected ones. "

msgctxt "sn1.37:1.3"
msgid "dasahi ca lokadhātūhi devatā yebhuyyena sannipatitā honti bhagavantaṃ dassanāya bhikkhusaṃghañca. "
msgstr "And most of the deities from ten solar systems had gathered to see the Buddha and the Saṅgha of mendicants. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn1.37:1.4"
msgid "Atha kho catunnaṃ suddhāvāsakāyikānaṃ devatānaṃ etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then four deities of the Pure Abodes, aware of what was happening, thought: "

msgctxt "sn1.37:1.5"
msgid "“ayaṃ kho bhagavā sakkesu viharati kapilavatthusmiṃ mahāvane mahatā bhikkhusaṃghena saddhiṃ pañcamattehi bhikkhusatehi sabbeheva arahantehi; "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn1.37:1.6"
msgid "dasahi ca lokadhātūhi devatā yebhuyyena sannipatitā honti bhagavantaṃ dassanāya bhikkhusaṃghañca. "
msgstr " "

#. VAR: paccekaṃ gāthaṃ → paccekagāthaṃ (bj, pts1-2) | paccekagāthā (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "sn1.37:1.7"
msgid "Yannūna mayampi yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkameyyāma; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavato santike paccekaṃ gāthaṃ bhāseyyāmā”ti. "
msgstr "“Why don’t we go to the Buddha and each recite a verse in his presence?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.56, sc2
msgctxt "sn1.37:2.1"
msgid "Atha kho tā devatā—seyyathāpi nāma balavā puriso samiñjitaṃ vā bāhaṃ pasāreyya pasāritaṃ vā bāhaṃ samiñjeyya; evameva—suddhāvāsesu devesu antarahitā bhagavato purato pāturahesuṃ. "
msgstr "Then, as easily as a strong person would extend or contract their arm, they vanished from the Pure Abodes and reappeared in front of the Buddha. "

msgctxt "sn1.37:2.2"
msgid "Atha kho tā devatā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhaṃsu. "
msgstr "They bowed to the Buddha and stood to one side. "

msgctxt "sn1.37:2.3"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ ṭhitā kho ekā devatā bhagavato santike imaṃ gāthaṃ abhāsi: "
msgstr "Standing to one side, one deity recited this verse in the Buddha’s presence: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn1.37:3.1"
msgid "“Mahāsamayo pavanasmiṃ, "
msgstr "“There’s a great congregation in the woods, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.37:3.2"
msgid "Devakāyā samāgatā; "
msgstr "a host of gods have assembled. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.37:3.3"
msgid "Āgatamha imaṃ dhammasamayaṃ, "
msgstr "We’ve come to this righteous congregation "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.37:3.4"
msgid "Dakkhitāye aparājitasaṅghan”ti. "
msgstr "to see the invincible Saṅgha!” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn1.37:4.1"
msgid "Atha kho aparā devatā bhagavato santike imaṃ gāthaṃ abhāsi: "
msgstr "Then another deity recited this verse in the Buddha’s presence: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "sn1.37:5.1"
msgid "“Tatra bhikkhavo samādahaṃsu, "
msgstr "“The mendicants there have immersion, "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: ujukaṃ akaṃsu → ujukamakaṃsu (bj, s1-3, km, pts1-2)
msgctxt "sn1.37:5.2"
msgid "Cittamattano ujukaṃ akaṃsu; "
msgstr "they’ve straightened out their own minds. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.37:5.3"
msgid "Sārathīva nettāni gahetvā, "
msgstr "Like a charioteer who has taken the reins, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.37:5.4"
msgid "Indriyāni rakkhanti paṇḍitā”ti. "
msgstr "the astute ones protect their senses.” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p>
#. REF: pts1ed1.27, sc6
msgctxt "sn1.37:6.1"
msgid "Atha kho aparā devatā bhagavato santike imaṃ gāthaṃ abhāsi: "
msgstr "Then another deity recited this verse in the Buddha’s presence: "

# NOTE: BB evidently reads khila here. But it seems to me more likely to be a synonym for paligha, i.e. khīla
#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "sn1.37:7.1"
msgid "“Chetvā khīlaṃ chetvā palighaṃ, "
msgstr "“Having cut the stake and cut the bar, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.37:7.2"
msgid "Indakhīlaṃ ūhacca manejā; "
msgstr "they’re unstirred, with boundary post uprooted. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.37:7.3"
msgid "Te caranti suddhā vimalā, "
msgstr "They live pure and immaculate, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.37:7.4"
msgid "Cakkhumatā sudantā susunāgā”ti. "
msgstr "the young dragons tamed by the seer.” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.57, sc8
msgctxt "sn1.37:8.1"
msgid "Atha kho aparā devatā bhagavato santike imaṃ gāthaṃ abhāsi: "
msgstr "Then another deity recited this verse in the Buddha’s presence: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc9
msgctxt "sn1.37:9.1"
msgid "“Ye keci buddhaṃ saraṇaṃ gatāse, "
msgstr "“Anyone who has gone to the Buddha for refuge "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.37:9.2"
msgid "Na te gamissanti apāyabhūmiṃ; "
msgstr "won’t go to a plane of loss. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.37:9.3"
msgid "Pahāya mānusaṃ dehaṃ, "
msgstr "After giving up this human body, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.37:9.4"
msgid "Devakāyaṃ paripūressantī”ti. "
msgstr "they swell the hosts of gods.”"

#. HTML: </p></blockquote></article></section></body></html>
